0K8)'-

33:30.080 --> 33:31.195
Thank you.

33:31.240 --> 33:32.389
We're not gonna shoot him.

33:32.440 --> 33:33.635
Excuse me?

33:33.720 --> 33:35.757
I don't like killing.

33:37.680 --> 33:39.114
Not unless I have to.

33:56.880 --> 33:58.234
So what now?

34:02.240 --> 34:04.709
I'm guessing
Miles is with your mom.

34:06.760 --> 34:07.795
Knowing him, he is.

34:10.480 --> 34:11.914
You're gonna go warn him.

34:14.920 --> 34:15.876
And I'm coming with you.

34:15.960 --> 34:17.951
Excuse me?

34:22.159 --> 34:23.355
You see this?

34:25.520 --> 34:28.273
Randall Flynn had a ring
with the exact same eye on it.

34:28.320 --> 34:30.436
If he's one of these guys,

34:30.520 --> 34:32.272
if they're half as bad
as what he was,

34:32.320 --> 34:34.391
we're all in trouble.

34:34.440 --> 34:38.149
And your family

34:38.239 --> 34:39.514
could use my help.

34:39.600 --> 34:41.398
Do you think
they want your help?

34:44.000 --> 34:45.149
No.

34:46.560 --> 34:47.789
But they're gonna need it.

34:47.880 --> 34:50.030
You're delusional.

34:51.880 --> 34:53.473
I'm walking away.

34:53.560 --> 34:55.915
And when I'm gone,
you won't be able to track me.

34:56.000 --> 34:59.470
So if you want to stop me,
shoot me.

35:33.440 --> 35:34.953
Hey, what's all this?

35:35.000 --> 35:36.149
Plan B.

35:39.440 --> 35:40.794
I'll be right behind you.

35:40.840 --> 35:42.638
I'll see you on the other side.

35:42.680 --> 35:44.478
That's exactly
what I said to my dad

35:44.560 --> 35:46.153
the night I told him
it was okay to die.

35:46.240 --> 35:47.719
That's great, Aaron.

35:47.800 --> 35:49.234
Sorry.

35:53.440 --> 35:54.350
Here it is.

35:54.440 --> 35:56.909
Last boat off the Titanic.

35:56.960 --> 35:58.439
Get on.

36:01.600 --> 36:02.556
Come with us.

36:02.680 --> 36:04.990
That's not the deal.

36:05.040 --> 36:07.316
Titus sees me on a wagon,
he will charge.

36:07.360 --> 36:08.475
I got to stay here.

36:08.560 --> 36:11.200
He finds his dead wife,
he comes for you.

36:12.200 --> 36:13.952
Well, let's just make sure
you're long gone by then.

36:18.000 --> 36:20.276
No. I'm not going.

36:20.320 --> 36:21.469
What?

36:21.560 --> 36:23.915
I went through too much
to save your life.

36:23.960 --> 36:25.678
I'm not gonna just let you die.

36:25.760 --> 36:27.876
- We don't have a choice.
- No, we do.

36:27.960 --> 36:29.473
We stay, we fight.

36:29.560 --> 36:30.994
We find a way out.

36:31.040 --> 36:33.156
Yeah? How?

36:33.240 --> 36:34.992
One hand tied behind my back?

36:35.040 --> 36:37.509
When this gets bad,
I'm not gonna be able to--

36:37.600 --> 36:38.874
Protect me?

36:38.920 --> 36:41.230
That it? Protect me?

36:41.280 --> 36:43.749
I don't need a martyr.
Miles, I need you.

36:43.840 --> 36:48.277
So, how about we just
protect each other, okay?

36:50.440 --> 36:54.559
This is all very touching,
but, Rachel, get on the wagon,

36:54.640 --> 36:56.472
or I swear to God,
I'm gonna throw you on.

